# E8: SQL pre-filter makes the in-Python scope re-check a constant-False branch.
# match_command_set_grant line 1683 grant.get("scope") != "COMMAND_SET":
# list_command_set_grants_agnostic SELECTs WHERE scope='COMMAND_SET', so the
# value is ALWAYS "COMMAND_SET". NotEq->Gt/Lt: '>'/'<' on equal strings = False
# like '!='. NotEq->Is: cosmic-ray substitutes '!=' with 'is' (NOT 'is not');
# the sqlite string is non-interned so 'is "COMMAND_SET"' is False like '!='.
# All three keep the branch False -> never skip -> identical. Line 1684 continue
# is then unreachable, so continue->break is unobservable.
6de4c76e8ff64ddfbe9ab68e6daab706
